    <h1>Ubiquitous Local ground surface weather data Aggregation and Processing</h1>
    <p class="lead" align="center">Smartphone-based ground weather observation and monitoring to detect localized heavy rainfall events for disaster warning</p>

    <%= image_tag("aboutCloud.png", class:"img-responsive", alt:"aboutCloud") %>
    
    <p>With rain-related hazards, it is difficult to forecast and prepare for it due to the decline in the availability and reliability of global daily weather reports. Therefore, we need to make use of available unconventional commercial sensors to provide supplementary information to existing systems. A more accurate and reliable weather forecast can then be made due to the prompt availability of information from ubiquitous devices. As smartphones become a widely used device, we propose a conceptual design of a multi-device ground weather observation network using smartphones and other sensors.</p>
